Mesosoma :
1.03 × as long as wide; mesoscutum reticulate with sparse setae laterally, 1.26 × as long as wide; notauli complete, broader apically, than basally; upper lateral pronotal area coriaceous; mesopleura with several longitudinal lines below tegula; mesopleural depression with a deep sulcus; metapleura bare anteriorly, posteriorly with very few white seate; scutellum 1.8 × as wide as long; (
Fig. 4
